That means:

Laws are written to protect corporate interests
The ARU is essentially corporate security with a badge
Any "public service" is really just maintaining the infrastructure that keeps profits flowing
Elections (if they even happen) are theater - the real power never changes hands

This makes the power dynamics crystal clear:

Skyreach = where the real decisions are made
Edgehaven and below = where those decisions are felt
Street-level players like Kai's crew have to navigate a system where the rule-makers are also the ones exploiting them

It also means Atlas Dynamics and AstraCore probably have representatives directly in this governing body, potentially in conflict with each other even while both maintaining the status quo that keeps them in power.
