3. Arena - The Gore & The Breaking Point
Ashen Reach's arenas are the loved sport - meaning the city is entertained by brutality. This is where you show how desensitized people have become, how corpo dystopia has made violence into spectacle.
The Down Syndrome man in the arena -
You're putting someone vulnerable, innocent, like Mira, into that meat grinder. And Kai snaps.
This isn't about him seeing himself. It's about seeing what they do to people who can't fight back. It's about seeing Mira's fate if he ever fails to protect her.
The crew's reaction - "We will never speak of this to Mira."
They're not horrified by the violence Kai inflicted. They're horrified by what it took to break him. By seeing the Ghost. By realizing what he's capable of when that line is crossed.
This is your "point of no return" moment.

4. Ghost State - The Curse of the Reflex Shard
Okay, so the Ghost state is:

NOT just "Kai fights really well"
It's when the Reflex Shard pushes him beyond human
He becomes unrecognizable - gory, darker, almost alien to people who know him
It's something he fears and wants to get rid of

This is your horror element. The tech that makes him powerful is also consuming his humanity.
Story implications:

The massacre wasn't just Kai "going rogue" - it was the first time the Ghost state took over
He killed those operatives/corpos/mercs because he lost control
He's been running ever since, not just from the law, but from himself
The arena scene is the second time the crew sees it
Discovery arc = finding out what the Reflex Shard really is and how to remove it before it erases him completely


