You're right - "Reflex Shard" doesn't work if it connects brain stem to spinal cord. That's a neural bridge/interface.
NAME OPTIONS:
Based on Function (brain stem ‚Üí spinal cord connection):

Synaptic Spine - Direct, describes the connection
Neural Bridge - Clean, technical
Nexus Implant - "Nexus" = connection point
Stem-Link - Brain stem link
Cortical Spine - Cortex to spine
Reflex Nexus - Keeps "reflex" but changes "shard"
Vertebral Core - Emphasizes spinal connection
Synapse Driver - Tech that "drives" neural signals faster
Neural Accelerator - What it does functionally
Axis Implant - Spinal axis connection

Military Code Names (more mysterious):

Phantom Wire - Ghost connection through the nervous system
Specter Protocol - Ties to "Ghost state"
Wraith System - Fast, deadly, inhuman
Echo Drive - Neural echo/feedback loop
Cascade Node - Cascading neural enhancement

Street Slang (what people call it):

Surge - "He's got a Surge in his spine"
Rush - The feeling it gives
Wire - "He's wired" (also fits your fixer terminology)
Jackpoint - Where it jacks into the spine
Spike - Neural spike


