Option A: Gig Gone Wrong

Routine merc job turns into ambush
Betrayed by client or caught in gang crossfire
Kai takes lethal damage - would die without immediate intervention
Stitch has the Surge prototype (acquired through black market? Found it? Doesn't know full specs?)
Installs it to save Kai's life

Option B: Past Catches Up

Someone from Ashen Reach finds Kai
Assassin, bounty hunter, or Atlas operative
Fight goes badly - Kai is outmatched (no Surge yet, fighting human)
Nearly dies
Stitch installs Surge in desperation

Option C: Protecting Mira

Threat against their home/Mira
Kai takes fatal damage defending her
Stitch installs Surge to save him - "You're not dying on her. Not today."

Option D: Brother's Doing (Indirect)

Brother sends someone after Kai (testing if he's alive? Tying up loose ends?)
Attack nearly kills Kai
Stitch saves him with Surge
Kai doesn't know brother was behind it yet

Which feels most true to your story?

